  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nHi, \r\nI recently used openzepplin-contracts/ERC20Burnable for my start-up Metarei.net, I found the code and documentation to be excellent thank you. Additionally I wanted to create demand for my token and provide a supplementary income by burning some tokens from each transfer. \r\n\r\nDoes this feature interest you? if so what are you expectations for the submission? I suppose: \r\n\r\n- contract\r\n- truffle tests\r\n- documentation\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nThe contract overrides ERC20 transfer method with a call to burn a specified fraction. It allows the owner to set the fraction that is burned and exposes a field which is a count of the total burned for the life of the contract.\r\n\r\nPlease see [ERC20BurnableTransfer](https://github.com/Metarei-network/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/ERC20BurnableTransfer/contracts/token/ERC20/extensions/ERC20BurnableTransfer.sol)\r\n\r\nThank you\r\n\r\nTom\r\n",
