    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hello @Metarei-network \r\n\r\nIMO your implementation is erroneous. By overriding transfer, you are designing your contract such that anyone could use `transferFrom` to bypass the burning mechanism.\r\n\r\nIf anyone was interested in doing burns on transfers, he should do that in the `_transfer` internal function. I'm pretty sure this has been discussed multiple time in the forum, with code example.\r\n\r\nOne of the reason we are not providing this, is we believe this is a dangerous thing to do, that might break interoperability with a lot of contracts that handle tokens. If you known what you are doing, understand the consequences, and do in depth compatibility testing ... then feel free to do it ... but we want to avoid less experienced devs from doing things that might have consequences they do not understand.",
